## Introduction

In this document we examine the relationship between *beak length* and *depth*.

## Data loading

The data used to answer this question can be found [here](https://allisonhorst.github.io/palmerpenguins/). Let's load the data.

```{r}
# Load the functions
source(here('R/functions.R'))

# Load the data
load(here('input/clean_data.rds'))

# Reformat categoric variables to factor
data <- data |> 
  mutate(
    species = as_factor(species),
    island = as_factor(island),
    sex = as_factor(sex)
  )
```

Let's inspect the data.
```{r}
#| echo: false
datatable(data, filter = "top")
```

## Descriptive analysis
This is a picture explaining **length** and **depth**. ![Culmen Depth](assets/culmen_depth.png){fig-align="left"}

```{r}
#| fig-cap: 'check this out'
#| fig-cap-location: margin
# Inspect summary
summary(data)

# Inspect means for Adelie species
data |> 
  filter(
    species == "Adelie"
  ) |> 
  group_by(
    island
  ) |> 
  summarise(
    M = mean(bill_length_mm, na.rm = T) |> round(2),
  )

# Draw scatterplot
p_scatterplot_dream_adelie <- build_scatterplot(data = data,
                  target_island = "Dream",
                  target_species = "Adelie")

plotly::ggplotly(p_scatterplot_dream_adelie)
```

```{r}
#| layout-ncol: 2

# Extract average bill length per specie
average_bill_length_by_specie <- data |> 
  group_by(
    species
  ) |> 
  summarise(
    `Average Bill Length`= mean(bill_length_mm, na.rm = T) |> round(2),
  )

# print table
kable(average_bill_length_by_specie)

# Extract average bill depth per specie
average_bill_depth_by_specie <- data |> 
  group_by(
    species
  ) |> 
  summarise(
    `Average Bill Depth` = mean(bill_depth_mm, na.rm = T) |> round(2),
  )

# Print table
kable(average_bill_depth_by_specie)
```

